chunks.html_content:
Limousines must be run by a licensed operator unless they’re being hired out without a driver.

For small limousines - seating up to 8 passengers - you’ll need a private hire vehicle (PHV) operator licence.

For large limousines - seating 9 passengers or more - you’ll need to get a public service vehicle (PSV) operator licence.
chunks.plain_content:
Limousine licensing
Limousines must be run by a licensed operator unless they’re being hired out without a driver.
For small limousines - seating up to 8 passengers - you’ll need a private hire vehicle (PHV) operator licence.
For large limousines - seating 9 passengers or more - you’ll need to get a public service vehicle (PSV) operator licence.

chunks.html_content: Operators hiring out limousines and drivers separately to avoid licensing are breaking the law.
chunks.plain_content:
Limousine licensing
Operators hiring out limousines and drivers separately to avoid licensing are breaking the law.

chunks.html_content: Stretched limousines must have Individual Vehicle Approval (IVA) to be registered and licensed. For those built before 29 July 2011, a Certificate of Initial Fitness (COIF) is accepted.
chunks.plain_content:
Limousine licensing
Vehicle standards
Stretched limousines must have Individual Vehicle Approval (IVA) to be registered and licensed. For those built before 29 July 2011, a Certificate of Initial Fitness (COIF) is accepted.

chunks.html_content: Limousines with up to 8 passenger seats do not require a licence for weddings and funerals.
chunks.plain_content:
Limousine licensing
Weddings and funerals
Limousines with up to 8 passenger seats do not require a licence for weddings and funerals.

chunks.html_content:
Your limousines can be destroyed or confiscated if you are not licensed or your vehicles are not properly insured. For other offences you can be prosecuted and fined.

Read guidance for operators of stretch limousines.
chunks.plain_content:
Limousine licensing
Fines and penalties
Your limousines can be destroyed or confiscated if you are not licensed or your vehicles are not properly insured. For other offences you can be prosecuted and fined.
Read guidance for operators of stretch limousines.
